cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for medical image analysis, specifically for the synthesis of missing MRI images in the presence of tumours. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of uncertainty estimates based on Monte Carlo dropout, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses the BraTS dataset, which is a widely used benchmark in medical image analysis and falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
